At 17 years old, Victor is preparing to go off to the University of Ingolstadt in Germany. Before he leaves his mother gets scarlet fever after caring for Elizabeth who also had it but recovered. Unfortunately, his mother is unable to recover and passes away. Her final request before she dies is for Elizabeth and Victor to get married.

&nbsp;

Victor heads off to school a few weeks after his mother's death and begins to meet his professors. He meets M. Krempe who is a professor of natural philosophy, but Victor dislikes him because he basically tells Victor that his time studying alchemy was a joke and it is useless. Another professor that Victor meets is a chemistry professor, Professor M. Waldman, and he sparks Victor's interest and leads him to studying science.

&nbsp;
